HEADWORD: Hindi
<hw>Hin"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prop. a Per. adj.
meaning, Indian, Hindoo.]</ety> <def>The name given by Europeans to that
form of the Hindustani language which is chiefly spoken by native
Hindus. In employs the Devanagari character, in which Sanskrit is
written.</def> <rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

